      ],
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "s",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The CFSocket object to modify. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "flags",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A bitwise-OR combination of flags controlling the behavior of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "s"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". See "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/1560944-cfsocket_flags"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " for the list of available flags."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "flags"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " argument controls whether callbacks of a given type are automatically reenabled after they are triggered, and whether the underlying native socket is closed when "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "s"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is invalidated."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To set and clear flags, you must set and mask bits in the flag set, respectively. First, call "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/1543754-cfsocketgetsocketflags"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", then modify the value returned. For example:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "    CFOptionFlags sockopt = CFSocketGetSocketFlags (mysock );",
            " ",
            "    /* Set the read callback to be automatically reenabled. */",
            "    sockopt |= kCFSocketAutomaticallyReenableReadCallBack;",
            " ",
            "    /* Clear the close-on-invalidate flag. */",
            "    sockopt &= ~kCFSocketCloseOnInvalidate;",
            " ",
            "    CFSocketSetSocketFlags(s, sockopt);"
          ],
          "syntax": "occ",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2556093",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "kCFSocketReadCallBack"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "kCFSocketAcceptCallBack"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "kCFSocketDataCallBack"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " callbacks are automatically reenabled after they are triggered, whereas "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "kCFSocketWriteCallBack"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " callbacks are not; "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "kCFSocketConnectCallBack"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " callbacks can only occur once, so they cannot be reenabled."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If a callback is automatically reenabled, it is called every time the condition becomes true. For example, a read callback is called as long as there is data on the socket waiting to be read. If a callback is not automatically reenabled, then it gets called exactly once, and is not called again until you manually reenable that callback by calling "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/1543029-cfsocketenablecallbacks"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Be careful about automatically reenabling read and write callbacks. If you do, the callbacks will be called repeatedly as long as the socket remains readable or writable, respectively."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Be sure to set these flags only for callback types that your CFSocket object actually possesses; the result of setting them for other callback types is undefined."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default the underlying native socket is closed when "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "s"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is invalidated. To disable that, clear (zero) the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "kCFSocketCloseOnInvalidate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " flag. This can be useful when you want to destroy a CFSocket object but continue to use the underlying native socket. The CFSocket object must still be invalidated when you no longer need it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Do not close the underlying native socket without invalidating the CFSocket object first."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
